## Daily Flow

1. Super opens apps.
2. Super+Space searches apps, files and actions.
3. Super+H returns here.
4. Super+N opens Wi-Fi/Bluetooth/audio/battery controls.
5. Super+E opens files.
6. `seven mini-os suggest` shows useful capabilities for the current context.

## Where To Find Information Locally

- `Super+H`: this documentation.
- `seven-help architecture`: open a chapter directly.
- `seven-help docs`: complete project documentation from `docs/`.
- `seven-help future`: future feature roadmap.
- `Super+Space`: search an app, action or file.
- `seven --help`: SevenOS commands.
- `seven actions`: user actions.
- `seven doctor`: system diagnostics.
- `seven status`: quick status.
- `docs/`: project documentation when the repository is present locally.

## Seven Server And Seven Core

Useful commands:

```bash
seven server status --json
seven server plan --json
seven server doctor
seven profile activate forge
seven-terminal forge
seven deploy inspect . --json
seven deploy dev .
seven deploy doctor .
seven deploy publish .
seven deploy publish . --provider cloudflare
seven deploy publish . --domain app.example.com
seven deploy domain app.example.com --target tunnel
seven deploy domain app.example.com --target vps --public-ip 203.0.113.10
seven deploy dns-check app.example.com --expected-ip 203.0.113.10
seven deploy dns-check app.example.com --expected-cname <tunnel-id>.cfargotunnel.com
seven deploy route-check app.example.com
seven deploy route-check my-project
seven deploy diagnose app.example.com
seven deploy diagnose my-project
seven deploy versions .
seven deploy rollback .
seven deploy remove .
seven deploy services --json
seven deploy panel --json
seven deploy status --json
seven core status --json
seven core health --json
seven core compact-bus --keep 5000 --json
seven shell status --json
seven shell doctor
scripts/shell-ags-runtime.sh status --json
scripts/shell-ags-runtime.sh report
scripts/shell-ags-runtime.sh open
./install.sh shell-ags-runtime --yes
```

Important rules:

- Seven Server stays local by default on `127.0.0.1`.
- Server and Deploy are Forge surfaces: development, services, logs and hosting run from `seven-terminal forge`.
- Outside Forge, `seven deploy ...` and `/deploy/*` return `sevenos.profile-gate.v1` with `seven profile activate forge` as the next action.
- `seven server status/plan/doctor` remain readable; `serve/start/stop/logs/install-user-service` require Forge.
- `seven deploy inspect . --json` gives Hub/Shell the project contract: stack, tools, dev/build/preview commands.
- `seven deploy publish .` creates a durable snapshot and a user systemd service that survives reboot.
- Every publish keeps a version; `seven deploy rollback .` returns to the previous version and `seven deploy remove .` deletes local hosting state.
- Without a domain, `--provider cloudflare` uses `cloudflared` when available to generate a public URL; with a domain, SevenOS prepares the explicit route.
- For a VPS, `seven deploy domain app.example.com --target vps --public-ip <ip>` shows A/AAAA records. For a personal machine without fixed public IP, `--target tunnel` explains the stable CNAME route.
- After DNS changes, `seven deploy dns-check app.example.com --expected-ip <ip>` or `--expected-cname <host>` verifies propagation.
- `seven deploy route-check <project-or-domain>` then verifies the full path: local service, DNS and public HTTP/HTTPS.
- `seven deploy diagnose <project-or-domain>` combines service, route, DNS, versions, score and next actions.
- Through Seven Server, the same contracts are available at `/deploy/domain`, `/deploy/dns-check`, `/deploy/route-check` and `/deploy/diagnose`.
- AGS is explicit: Seven Shell uses AUR package `aylurs-gtk-shell`; do not install AUR package `ags`, which is Adventure Game Studio.
- The AGS route supports `--dry-run`, `--yes`, `--json`, writes
  `~/.local/state/sevenos/shell/ags-runtime-report.json` and can open in Seven
  Terminal with `scripts/shell-ags-runtime.sh open`.
- A non-local bind is refused unless `SEVENOS_SERVER_EXPOSE_UNSAFE=1` is set, because auth/TLS/policy broker are not public yet.
- Seven Core should report `RUNTIME_READY` when `seven-daemon.service` and `seven-context-observer.service` are running.
- The current SevenBus remains a local JSONL journal; `seven core compact-bus` archives the old journal and keeps the latest events.
EOF
  fi

  append_future_features
  append_docs_reference
}

append_future_features() {
  if [[ "$LANG_CODE" == "fr" ]]; then
    cat >> "$HELP_DOC" <<'EOF'

## Features futures

Cette section sépare les fonctions déjà utilisables des directions futures.
SevenOS doit rester honnête : une feature future ne doit pas être présentée
comme disponible dans les surfaces grand public tant qu'elle n'a pas de commande,
de test et de chemin de retour.

| Domaine | Direction | État |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Installateur public | installation disque plus guidée, avec Calamares/Archinstall et checks SevenOS | planifié |
| SevenRepo | dépôt SevenOS pour paquets, thèmes, helpers et composants natifs | réservé |
| Seven Core | daemon Rust plus complet, événements locaux, santé système et contrats stables | runtime local |
| SevenBus | bus local pour contexte, actions et événements sans parser le shell | journal JSONL, IPC typé ensuite |
| SevenAI | assistant local-first plus profond, playbooks, diagnostics et explications | progressif |
| Seven Shell | couche shell plus native, rapide et maintenable | progressif |
| Store | permissions Flatpak, recommandations locales et vues par mini OS | progressif |
| Baobab | packs culturels, langues africaines, cartes et collections offline | progressif |
| Atlas Explorer | documents, cartes, OCR et recherche locale | actif |
| Cloud personnel | synchronisation volontaire, backup, déploiement et serveur local | futur |
| Performance | politiques systemd slices/uclamp exposées mais jamais silencieuses | futur |

Règles pour ajouter une feature future :

- documenter l'intention dans `docs/` ;
- exposer une commande de status ou de plan avant une commande destructive ;
- ajouter un test dans `scripts/ux-check.sh` ou un doctor ciblé ;
- garder une UX compréhensible pour le grand public ;
- ne pas casser Equinox comme profil admin/hôte ;
- ne pas affaiblir l'isolation des mini OS.

EOF
  else
    cat >> "$HELP_DOC" <<'EOF'

## Future Features

This section separates usable features from future direction. SevenOS should stay
honest: a future feature must not look available in public surfaces until it has
a command, a check and a recovery path.

| Area | Direction | State |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Public installer | more guided disk install through Calamares/Archinstall and SevenOS checks | planned |
| SevenRepo | SevenOS repository for packages, themes, helpers and native components | reserved |
| Seven Core | deeper Rust daemon, local events, system health and stable contracts | local runtime |
| SevenBus | local bus for context, actions and events without shell scraping | JSONL journal, typed IPC next |
| SevenAI | deeper local-first assistant, playbooks, diagnostics and explanations | progressive |
| Seven Shell | more native, fast and maintainable shell layer | progressive |
| Store | Flatpak permissions, local recommendations and mini OS views | progressive |
| Baobab | cultural packs, African languages, maps and offline collections | progressive |
| Atlas Explorer | documents, maps, OCR and local research | active |
| Personal cloud | opt-in sync, backup, deployment and local server workflows | future |
| Performance | visible systemd slice/uclamp policies, never silent changes | future |

Rules for adding a future feature:

- document the intention in `docs/`;
- expose a status or plan command before a destructive command;
- add a test in `scripts/ux-check.sh` or a focused doctor;
- keep the UX understandable for the general public;
- keep Equinox as the admin/host profile;
- do not weaken mini OS isolation.

EOF
  fi
}

append_docs_reference() {
  [[ -d "$ROOT_DIR/docs" ]] || return 0
  ROOT_DIR="$ROOT_DIR" HELP_DOC="$HELP_DOC" LANG_CODE="$LANG_CODE" python - <<'PY'
import os
from pathlib import Path

root = Path(os.environ["ROOT_DIR"])
help_doc = Path(os.environ["HELP_DOC"])
lang = os.environ.get("LANG_CODE", "en")
docs = sorted((root / "docs").glob("*.md"), key=lambda path: path.name.lower())

if not docs:
    return_code = 0
else:
    with help_doc.open("a", encoding="utf-8") as out:
        if lang == "fr":
            out.write("\n## Documentation projet\n\n")
            out.write("Cette section reprend automatiquement le contenu complet du dossier `docs/` pour que le helper serve de référence locale sur l'architecture SevenOS.\n\n")
            out.write("Les documents stratégiques peuvent mentionner des éléments futurs. Quand un passage parle de `future`, `planned`, `scaffold` ou `preview`, il décrit une direction ou une fondation, pas forcément une fonction prête pour le grand public.\n\n")
        else:
            out.write("\n## Project Documentation\n\n")
            out.write("This section automatically includes the full `docs/` directory so the helper can act as the local SevenOS architecture reference.\n\n")
            out.write("Strategic documents may mention future pieces. When a passage says `future`, `planned`, `scaffold` or `preview`, it describes direction or foundation work, not always a finished public feature.\n\n")

        out.write("| Document | Title |\n| --- | --- |\n")
        titles = {}
        for path in docs:
            title = path.stem.replace("_", " ").replace("-", " ").title()
            for raw in path.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="ignore").splitlines():
                if raw.startswith("# "):
                    title = raw[2:].strip()
                    break
            titles[path.name] = title
            out.write(f"| `{path.name}` | {title} |\n")

        for path in docs:
            text = path.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="ignore").strip()
            if not text:
                continue
            title = titles.get(path.name, path.stem)
            out.write(f"\n## docs/{path.name}\n\n")
            out.write(f"_Source locale : `docs/{path.name}`._\n\n" if lang == "fr" else f"_Local source: `docs/{path.name}`._\n\n")
            for line in text.splitlines():
                if line.startswith("#"):
                    level = len(line) - len(line.lstrip("#"))
                    content = line[level:].strip()
                    out.write(f"{'#' * min(level + 2, 6)} {content}\n")
                else:
                    out.write(line + "\n")
            out.write("\n")
PY
}

write_docs_index() {
  mkdir -p "$STATE_DIR"
  ROOT_DIR="$ROOT_DIR" HELP_DOC="$HELP_DOC" LANG_CODE="$LANG_CODE" python - <<'PY'
import os
from pathlib import Path

root = Path(os.environ["ROOT_DIR"])
help_doc = Path(os.environ["HELP_DOC"])
lang = os.environ.get("LANG_CODE", "en")
docs = sorted((root / "docs").glob("*.md"), key=lambda path: path.name.lower())

with help_doc.open("w", encoding="utf-8") as out:
    if lang == "fr":
        out.write("# Index documentation SevenOS\n\n")
        out.write("Utilise `seven-help doc <nom>` pour ouvrir un seul document, par exemple `seven-help doc architecture`.\n\n")
    else:
        out.write("# SevenOS Documentation Index\n\n")
        out.write("Use `seven-help doc <name>` to open one document, for example `seven-help doc architecture`.\n\n")
    out.write("| Document | Title | Command |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n")
    for path in docs:
        title = path.stem.replace("_", " ").replace("-", " ").title()
        for raw in path.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="ignore").splitlines():
            if raw.startswith("# "):
                title = raw[2:].strip()
                break
        key = path.stem.lower()
        out.write(f"| `{path.name}` | {title} | `seven-help doc {key}` |\n")
PY
}

write_single_project_doc() {
  local query="${*:-}"
  [[ -n "${query// /}" ]] || return 2
  mkdir -p "$STATE_DIR"
  ROOT_DIR="$ROOT_DIR" HELP_DOC="$HELP_DOC" LANG_CODE="$LANG_CODE" DOC_QUERY="$query" python - <<'PY'
import os
import re
import sys
from pathlib import Path

root = Path(os.environ["ROOT_DIR"])
help_doc = Path(os.environ["HELP_DOC"])
lang = os.environ.get("LANG_CODE", "en")
query = os.environ.get("DOC_QUERY", "").strip()
docs = sorted((root / "docs").glob("*.md"), key=lambda path: path.name.lower())

def key(value: str) -> str:
    return re.sub(r"[^a-z0-9]+", "", value.lower())

query_key = key(query)
matches = []
for path in docs:
    title = path.stem
    text = path.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="ignore")
    for raw in text.splitlines():
        if raw.startswith("# "):
            title = raw[2:].strip()
            break
    haystacks = {key(path.name), key(path.stem), key(title)}
    if query_key in haystacks or any(query_key and query_key in item for item in haystacks):
        matches.append((path, title, text))

if not matches:
    with help_doc.open("w", encoding="utf-8") as out:
        if lang == "fr":
            out.write(f"# Document introuvable: {query}\n\n")
            out.write("Documents disponibles:\n\n")
        else:
            out.write(f"# Document Not Found: {query}\n\n")
            out.write("Available documents:\n\n")
        for path in docs:
            out.write(f"- `{path.name}`\n")
    sys.exit(2)

path, title, text = matches[0]
with help_doc.open("w", encoding="utf-8") as out:
    out.write(f"# {title}\n\n")
    out.write(f"_Source locale : `docs/{path.name}`._\n\n" if lang == "fr" else f"_Local source: `docs/{path.name}`._\n\n")
    skipped_title = False
    skip_next_blank = False
    for line in text.strip().splitlines():
        if skip_next_blank and not line.strip():
            skip_next_blank = False
            continue
        skip_next_blank = False
        if line.startswith("#"):
            level = len(line) - len(line.lstrip("#"))
            content = line[level:].strip()
            if not skipped_title and level == 1 and key(content) == key(title):
                skipped_title = True
                skip_next_blank = True
                continue
            out.write(f"{'#' * min(level + 1, 6)} {content}\n")
        else:
            out.write(line + "\n")
PY
}

show_generated_doc() {
  if [[ "${SEVENOS_DRY_RUN:-0}" == "1" ]]; then
    cat "$HELP_DOC"
    return 0
  fi
  local viewer=""
  if command -v less >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    viewer="less -R $(printf '%q' "$HELP_DOC")"
  elif command -v bat >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    viewer="bat --paging=always --style=plain --language=markdown $(printf '%q' "$HELP_DOC")"
  else
    viewer="cat $(printf '%q' "$HELP_DOC")"
  fi
  run_terminal "$viewer"
}

